Skirmisher.unitDescription: Anti-archer Skirmisher that cannot attack at close range. Strong vs. Ranged Soldiers and Spearman-line. Weak vs. units at close range.

Slinger.unitDescription: Inca unique anti-infantry Skirmisher that cannot attack at close range. Strong vs. Infantry. Weak vs. Ranged Soldiers and Cavalry.

Spearman.unitDescription: Anti-cavalry Infantry. Strong vs. Mounted Units, especially elephants. Weak vs. Ranged Soldiers and Infantry.

Steppe Lancer.unitDescription: Light Horseman with increased attack range. Strong in groups. Weak vs. Cavalry, Camel Riders and Archery Units.

Tarkan.unitDescription: Hunnic unique Heavy Cavalry. Exceptionally strong vs. buildings. Weak vs. Spearman-line and Camel Riders.

Teutonic Knight.unitDescription: Teutonic unique Infantry with exceptional melee armor. Slow but resistant to conversion. Strong vs. melee units. Weak vs. Archery Units and Gunners.

Thirisadai.unitDescription: Dravidian unique Warship with high durability. Strong vs. most Warships. Weak vs. Fire Ships.

Throwing Axeman.unitDescription: Frankish unique Infantry with ranged melee attack. Strong vs. Infantry. Weak vs. Archery Units and Siege Weapons.

Tiger Cavalry.unitDescription: Wei unique Cavalry that gains HP and attack when defeating enemy military. Exceptionally strong vs. Ranged Soldiers. Weak vs. Spearman-line.

Traction Trebuchet.unitDescription: Powerful anti-building Siege Weapon with long range, but cannot attack enemies at close range. Strong vs. buildings. Can attack ground and destroy trees.

Trebuchet.unitDescription: Powerful anti-building Siege Weapon with exceptional range. Must be packed to move, unpacked to attack. Cannot attack enemies at close range. Strong vs. buildings. Can attack ground and destroy trees.

Turtle Ship.unitDescription: Korean unique Siege Warship with high armor and attack. Strong vs. most Warships and buildings. Weak vs. Fire Ships.

Two-Handed Swordsman.unitDescription: All-purpose Infantry. Strong vs. buildings, Infantry, Scout Cavalry- and Skirmisher-line. Weak vs. Ranged Soldiers at long range.

Urumi Swordsman.unitDescription: Dravidian unique Infantry with a charged blast attack. Strong vs. buildings and units at close range. Weak vs. Ranged Soldiers at long range.

War Chariot.unitDescription: Shu unique Siege Cavalry with rapid-fire attack, but cannot attack at close range. Has long reload time. Can switch to a barrage mode that covers more area but is less accurate. Strong vs. Ranged Soldiers. Weak vs. Cavalry and Siege Weapons.

War Elephant.unitDescription: Persian unique Cavalry that deals trample damage. Strong vs. buildings and units at close range. Weak vs. Spearman-line and Monks.

War Galley.unitDescription: All-purpose Warship with ranged attack. Strong vs. units at long range. Weak vs. Fire Ships.

War Wagon.unitDescription: Korean unique Mounted Archer. Slow but durable. Strong vs. Infantry and Archery Units. Weak vs. Spearman-line, Skirmishers and Camel Riders.

Warrior Priest.unitDescription: Armenian unique Monastery Infantry that can heal friendly units. Can collect Relics and bring them to Monasteries. Strong vs. Infantry. Weak vs. Scout Cavalry-line and Archery Units.

White Feather Guard.unitDescription: Shu unique Infantry that temporarily slows down the unit it attacks. Strong vs. Cavalry and Infantry. Weak vs. Ranged Soldiers.

Winged Hussar.unitDescription: Polish and Lithuanian unique fast moving Light Horseman for scouting and raiding. Resistant to conversion. Exceptionally strong vs. Monastery Units. Weak vs. Spearman-line and Camel Riders.

Woad Raider.unitDescription: Celtic unique Infantry with fast movement speed. Strong vs. Infantry and Siege Weapons. Weak vs. Archery Units and Cavalry.

Xianbei Raider.unitDescription: Wei unique Mounted Archer with a charged ranged attack. Strong vs. Infantry. Weak vs. Skirmishers and Camel Riders.

Xolotl Warrior.unitDescription: Mesoamerican cavalry unit. Strong vs. infantry and siege. Weak vs. Pikemen and Camel Riders.
